    <description><![CDATA[<h1>使用动作</h1>

<h2>1.编辑动作模型</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 动作也是模型，理论上任何一个模型都可以转化为动作来执行，所以编辑动作的方法就是编辑模型的方法。</p>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 动作可以作为单独的应用也可以作为其它模型的行为。动作作为单独应用时，常常使用xworker.lang.ActionThing模型来编写。作为对象的行为时则可以在任何一个模型里编写。</p>

<h2>2.获取动作</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 动作也是模型，可以首先获取模型，然后再转化为动作。如下面的Groovy代码。</p>

<pre class="brush:groovy;">
import org.xmeta.Action;
import org.xmeta.Thing;

//获取动作模型
Thing thing = world.getThing(&quot;xworker.example.action._actions.HelloWorld&quot;);

//转化为动作
Action action = thing.getAction();</pre>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 也可以直接通过World获取动作，World的getAction()方法内部也是先获取模型再转化为动作。</p>

<pre class="brush:groovy;">
import org.xmeta.Action;

Action action = world.getAction(&quot;xworker.example.action._actions.HelloWorld&quot;);</pre>

<h2>3.执行动作</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 获取动作后就可以用来执行了，执行前需要先准备好执行环境，即动作上下文。</p>

<pre class="brush:groovy;">
import org.xmeta.Action;
import org.xmeta.ActionContext;
import org.xmeta.Thing;

//获取动作模型
Thing thing = world.getThing(&quot;xworker.example.action._actions.HelloWorld&quot;);

//转化为动作
Action action = thing.getAction();

//准备运行环境，创建动作上下文
ActionContext ac = new ActionContext();

//执行动作
action.run(ac);</pre>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
]]></description>
    <en_description><![CDATA[<h1>Use action</h1>

<h2>1.Edit action model</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Action is also a model. In theory, any model can be transformed into action to execute, so the method of editing action is the method of editing model.</p>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Action can be used as a standalone application or as the behavior of other models. Action is often used as a standalone application <strong>xworker.lang.ActionThing</strong> model. As the behavior of an object, it can be written in any model.</p>

<h2>2.Get action</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Action is also a model. You can get the model first and then convert it into action. Like the groovy code below.</p>

<pre class="brush:groovy;">
import org.xmeta.Action;
import org.xmeta.Thing;

//Get an action model
Thing thing = world.getThing(&quot;xworker.example.action._actions.HelloWorld&quot;);

//Convert to action
Action action = thing.getAction();</pre>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Actions can also be obtained directly through the world. The getaction () method of the world first obtains the model and then converts it into actions.</p>

<pre class="brush:groovy;">
import org.xmeta.Action;

Action action = world.getAction(&quot;xworker.example.action._actions.HelloWorld&quot;);</pre>

<h2>3.Execute action</h2>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After obtaining the action, it can be used for execution. Before execution, you need to prepare the execution environment, that is, the action context.</p>

<pre class="brush:groovy;">
import org.xmeta.Action;
import org.xmeta.ActionContext;
import org.xmeta.Thing;

//Get an action model
Thing thing = world.getThing(&quot;xworker.example.action._actions.HelloWorld&quot;);

//Convert to action
Action action = thing.getAction();

//Prepare the running environment and create the action context
ActionContext ac = new ActionContext();

//Execute action
action.run(ac);</pre>

<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
]]></en_description>
